reviews.text: If you're looking for a classy venue that is experienced with bringing in outside vendors and lets you bring in your own alcohol, the Historic Dekalb Courthouse in downtown Decatur, GA is perfect! The venue is well-suited to hold a ceremony, reception, cocktail hour, caterers, photography, or anything else you might need. They're prepared and easy to work with. Not to mention the location - the courthouse is surrounded by hotels, transportation, and restaurants, which makes the visit easy for your guests. I have NO regrets about choosing the courthouse, and would do it again in a heartbeat.
Nice little place. The display of ranch house development is worth the visit. The quarry photos are icing on the cupcake.
Really enjoyed seeing some of my Dad & Grand-Dad's history.

Parking was a bit of a challenge but worth the effort. We attended a wedding at the Historic Dekalb Courthouse. So much more than we expected. Such a wonderful location. Lots of thinnd to do and places to visit. QUITE HISTORIC. We plan to return
Visited this venue looking for a spot to host a wedding reception. The space is really old, dusty, damp, dated and it's not really functional from a logistics standpoint.  Parking is a nightmare.
Awesome school (I attended there). Just came back from their homecoming. It was a blast. Emory really know how to throw a party. The school offers excellent and rigorous courses.

Emory is a joke! They keep posting the same jobs up on indeed and linkedin but don’t even hire for those specific positions. Your application will be pending for months! It is so ridiculous! They don’t even have a Hiring Manager to contact about the status of your application. Just a waste of time don’t bother!

There is a great community at Emory. Teachers and classes are very interesting. Food is decent. Dorms are very nice and rooms are pretty spacious. There is lots of support and people to guide and help you as you transition in your first year. Lots of programs and events all the time to keep you busy and to enjoy with friends! Great university!!!

Dealing with Talent Acquisition was the worse. I had a talent manager earlier last year, named Peter Cuomo. When he was speaking with me about my offer he was completely unprofessional,abrasive and condescending.
Emory performing arts was superb music and dance.

Went to one of their open nights and it was fantastic. The planetarium is really cool, although the planetarium show was a little bit lackluster. The staff was friendly and patient. You can definitely tell they like what they do. The atmosphere feels more like a school (because it is) but I didn't mind that much.
Cool little place. Clearly a lot of attention to detail in the design. Stand in the center of the circle for a strange surprise!
Great place to learn more about astronomy
Great location
Really liked the mosaic on the plaza.

My favorite French restaurant to eat at in the Atlanta metro area. Food is delicious, fresh, and quick. Atmosphere is very homely and welcoming. It is owned and operated by a little French family. Very sweet people. Prices are great too for the quality of the food.

The environment is incredibly charming. Our server was fast and cordial, even while serving everyone else in the cafe herself. I had a sandwich with chicken and pesto, along with some lentil soup. Simply divine! And the espresso I had afterwards was amazing. I'm not going to forget this place anytime soon.

Authentic Alsace
I don't know how they do it. But this place is an absolute diamond in the rough gem.
Movies are made from places like this.
One of the most memorable service experience at a restaurant so far. Excellent service! Excellent!

We were in Atlanta on vacation and decided to try this restaurant. We are so glad we took the time to come here. This place is adorable and delicious. The seating is limited but we never felt rushed by our server to order or leave after we were done. We brought our two young children and even they enjoyed the food. The wine list isn't extensive, but it's a nice selection for a small restaurant. I would highly recommend this to anyone visiting Atlanta. I know I will be back.

The food!  They have Beef Wellington!  I have died and gone to heaven.  

Americans, when they hear "French Restaurant" think fancy.  This place is not. It's "quaint". Or "charming".  It's a "tastefully appointed" hole in the wall.  You'd be lucky to notice it even if you were walking by it.  It is small.  Tiny.

But the food!  It's not just the Beef Wellington.  Everybody at the table (party of 4) raved about their dinner. I can't wait to eat there again.  If I could manage to get there for breakfast on a sunny day to eat and have coffee on the sidewalk, I'm sure I'd give them 5 stars.  Alas, I live over an hour away.  But I'll be back anyway.
The tapas are amazing.  Loved the bacon wrapped dates! We were there on National Paella Day and I have seriously never had better.  Good stuff and worth a return

This restaurant is very popular on weekends and reservations are highly recommended. I am usually not a fan of tapas as I find them expensive and leave hungry but the Iberian pig is an exception. The food was great and I thought it was well priced. The service was great but the kitchen was slow. We waited about 40 minutes to get our food and then it seemed to all come at once. Maybe try to space out your orders if you can. In the end it was great food, good service and nice ambiance.

One if my favorite spots in Atlanta.  Your best bet is to walk in and tell them to feed you.  They bring out an assortment of items that taste great and by the end of our meal the whole group was smiling.  We had a couple of dietary restrictions and they adapted for those guests with ease.  Cozy dining room that while crowded didn't feel like it was so.

One of my favorites in Atlanta.  They have food for all tastes and dietary needs.  We had the octopus, scallops and sword fish, all outstanding.  The potato bravado are always special.  Bacon wrapped dates and roast pork dish.  We finished with the churos with ice cream.  Great food.

Best Spanish tapas restaurant in Atlanta. Bacon wrapped dates are life-changing. Port menu is long and distinguished. Great wine list, by the glass and bottles, especially Spanish reds. Everything on the menu is good, with great specials. Atmosphere is lively. Great for groups from 2 couples to 10 people, the more the marrier. Fun to let each person contribute to the order. Good for vegetarians as well. Bar is great as well. Close to my favorite restaurant in the Atlanta area.

Got idea to eat here from Co workers. Got my order to go, had everything put on the side. My food was the best. Loved everything. Service was great, food great, Price great, vibe great. Nice place to meet family or friends for dinner and drinks.👍👍

Really enjoyed the patio dining. It is really too bad about the parking situation. That is the only bad thing I can say. I don't think that we will be back because of the parking. My mother and sister are handicapped. It's bad enough that we have to pull around back to unload everyone then I get a $20 parking ticket for parking in a space that was unmarked. Where are the handicapped spots. Thanks again for the great food. Get the parking situation fixed and we will be back. Don't look for us again until the parking situation is changed, thanks.

I failed to get a picture and I wish I hadn't because they make some gigantic burritos. My lady and I split one and I was full off of my halve alone. They bring out chips and dip that's on the house and I swear it's the best version of that I've seen anywhere. The chips are actually seasoned and not the bland ones most places serve. It's what I call getting a whole lot for little when it comes to pricing. You're in downtown Decatur so expect the atmosphere to be great. Definitely recommend this place!

Nice concept with some not so nice food. When you come to the restaurant, expect to be there for a while. This means find some better parking then the overpriced parking lot next to it. Then there's the food. The options in the menu are almost limitless. However, they are not so flavorful. The international varieties of burritos are ultimately flavorless. It taste like water with a hint of vegetables. The only thing worth eating there was the chips and salsa. They claim to travel the world on order to make great burritos but the flavor is anything but great.

Best Burrito anywhere. Way better than the bland Bell Street Burritos. After enjoying Raging Burrito's great chips and salsas, we ended up splitting a Cajun Killer Burrito. Excellent service, great food and amazing patio! Keeps us coming back!

Excellent service on a busy Saturday night. We were seated right at the time if our reservation, ordered quickly and had our food within 15 minutes. Our waitress was impeccable - professional, friendly, knew the menu, made helpful suggestions and made sure we always had plenty of water. 

The Burger Stack was priced at $14 but worth every penny. A simple burger with cheese and pickles and a delicious bun. What made it perfect was the excellent service if the meat and the tender, juicy patty. It was one of the best I've had. The fries were perfectly fried, crispy with a touch of salt.

We ordered three desserts - seasonal cheesecake, rice pudding and Brooklyn blackout cake. All three were fantastic, but my family's favorites were the seasonal cheesecake and the rice pudding.

The atmosphere is casual and relaxed. They played great music, that didn't overwhelm our conversation but was a nice addition to the environment. It's more of a cafe style, so not a formal dining experience but perfect for a casual date or family outing when you want quality food in a nice place.

Stopped by recently for breakfast on a weekday and it was perfect! Not too busy so easy to get a comfortable table and have a casual conversation. Lots of business people on laptops and having meetings. 

Service was quick and friendly. Food was tasty and well priced. 

Next time I’ll be sure to check out the pastries because the TGM bread looks delicious too!

Cool place. I had the pastrami sandwich which was very good. It's not on the brunch menu but they still serve it. A bit strange to figure that out but glad I did. The sandwich was great but too fatty. I enjoy fat so I cut off half of it and then it was perfect. My finance had a bagel with salmon, cucumber and red caviar. It was good but we'd skip the caviar next time, the quality was not what we are used too. Also the line was very long on a Saturday for brunch, keep that in mind.

Everything here is so fresh!! The venture is beautiful, boasting high ceilings and an marble bar tops. The menu item may appear simple but   you can taste the quality of the ingredients, they never disappoint. This place is great for lighter meals that will fill you up.

The General is as good as this style gets...very popular among both Emory and CDC located patrons. I had their famous Reuben: fabulous and bountiful. Very good and pleasant service. You will enjoy this... Lots of history, too, about the namesake ship that brought thousands of refugees to the US following WWII.
Fun little shop with locally made art and other crafts. Recommend the visit even just for fun
Many artists represented at this consignment gallery, wide variety of styles and goods.  Some items seem a bit pricey, but most reasonable.  Knowledgeable sales staff.
Owners make you feel welcome unique, original items
I came from new York and stay in place until I left to go home.  I brought and brought...lol
Fun atmosphere with great local artists. Friendly, helpful sales ladies will assist you in finding a perfect piece of art for your home.

Real cool cozy spot. Solid beer list, and short but interesting food menu. The umami fries were great as were the wings, which also were portioned generously for the price. My wife got the fried chicken sandwich and I tried a bite of the chicken -- top notch. Will be back for sure.

Great neighborhood “Whiskey” bar in Oakhurst. Located close to Decatur, this a great place to hangout. The food is fantastic on an ever rotating menu full of seasonal offerings. They also have a variety of craft beer available and yes whiskey. Reminds me of a true Irish pub.

They have a great little patio are that is perfect for having a couple of cocktails or especially nice to enjoy brunch. Order the Chinese breakfast complete with crispy pork belly. 

A secret tip... order the house burger (it’s off menu) complete with bacon, fresh jalapeños and pimento cheese. Oh Yeah! 

And, if you’re in the neighborhood... they throw one hell of a good party on St. Paddy’s day; live music, drink specials and give aways.

Plus Code- QM5W+PG Decatur, Georgia

Love the atmosphere.  It’s small/intimate vibe - great place to chit chat with friends.  Went for brunch and the food was great.  I went with Leah’s favorite.  My friend had the steak and eggs special- which was also fantastic.  Serve was “ok” - had to ask for everything vs being offered.  Other than that - no complaints.

The food was amazing and my Bloody Mary fantastic. Being the best weather we’ve seen, it was also a bonus that we could sit outside. I sadly, however, cannot give 5 stars. We ordered two small dishes to share because we intended to have dinner a couple hours later. The server accidentally put in the order incorrectly. He explained this, and offered us the dish in his hand while we waited for the initial order. As a server, I understood he offered this because he can’t return it to the kitchen anymore, and that it would be thrown away. We said, “sure!” and shared it as a group. When we got our bill we were charged for the dish no one wanted.

So this review is about 3 months past due. I ordered fish and chips. I googled for the best fish & chips and Atlanta magazine rated this place one of the best. Well, my bread battered, thickly battered I might add fish had absolutely no flavor. The fries were ok I had 1 piece aaaaaa more like a half of a piece of fish and paid 16 bucks for it. Will never order here again. Oh and btw never trusting a  magazine suggestion again, I'll b my own judge.

One of my favorite Indian restaurants. I've been coming here for about 5 years now and the quality of my meal every time is consistent. Never much of wait time, which can be difficult to find in Atlanta. I also love one of the newer servers they hired, Gabrielle. Each time I come she is warm and welcoming and we're always laughing about something. If anyone from management is reading this, she's definitely a keeper! #staycrispy 😉
Great food. A different take to the menu and the options presented. Service could be a bit faster though.
Authentic Indian food with great flavours and spices. Definitely worth if you want to try the real Indian food.

This is without a doubt the best Indian food in Atlanta. It's all amazing. You won't be let down, and it is rarely crowded for weekday lunch. Don't all start going though, I like not having a line. But really it's amazing.
Will definitely be back. Great authentic Indian meal at reasonable prices. The only downside is the parking in this lot..... not a lot for all the shops there.

I ate at Rise-n-Dine a couple of months ago and meant to write a review then, but got delayed, so here it is.

Rise-n-Dine is Fantastic!! It starts with the way you are treated while awaiting your table. They offer you coffee while you wait!

Then the service at the table and the food are both some of the best I have ever gotten at any breakfast restaurant I have ever been to.

The management is very hands on and makes sure everything is perfect.

I highly recommend Rise-n-Dine. You won't be disappointed!!

Had yet another great experience at Rise and Dine today. Was asked if we were ok with sharing a community table..if so we could be seated sooner..we said yes. So we dined with 2 great individuals we would have never had the opportunity to meet otherwise. Great food..great company.. great service. We will be back.

Let me start by saying this place serves the best drip coffee of any breakfast joint and most dedicated coffee shops.  That alone is enough to keep me and the family coming back time and again.  I don't have any experience with their sandwiches but their breakfast fare is top notch with plenty of variety.  It can get quite busy but they are extremely efficient and the wait is usually not too bad even with a full house.  That said, the indoor waiting area is pretty small which can be an issue if the weather isn't great.  Service is typically excellent and food comes out quickly so it's a great  place to go with kids.

I don't know what else to say.  We love Rise-n-Dine and it's usually at least a once-a-week trip for my family.  Don't miss out!

Hands down the best breakfast/lunch spot in the Decatur area. Always fresh, always delicious, and always served with a smile! The menu has something for everyone, even my picky boyfriend who eats salad for breakfast! The chicken sausage is my "must have" breakfast item, but I love everything I've tried! Highly recommend!
Quaint and cute. Great location. The food options are healthy and tasty. Great place to meet up with friends to catch up and share a bite to eat.
We had 2 dinner in week with family & friends and food was owsome. Love to visit here. Nice place for food lovers.
Quality has improved each time and the servers are much more nicer and friendly! Great place for Indo-Asian food

I really don’t know what want to give even a star to this restaurant but I am doing it because of quality of food that chef makes.  I think he or she should find another owner or a partner and open up his or her own restaurant.  I will be surprised if people still would come to this restaurant in that case. Let me tell you this, who would charge 15% gratuity for two adults and three kids younger than nine years for total number of items less than three. The service is awful. We ordered IPG mule with the request to the server to make it a little stronger.  When we received the bill it was charged twice the price. Even in Chicago downtown, I did not pay for $22 a mule. Responsible server should have made this clear upon receipt of an order. It is of no surprise that the restaurant cannot provide a professional service to their patrons.  If not for the company. I would not have come to this restaurant again. But as I said before, chef does a wonderful job keeping up with the taste for Indian Chinese food, guess what, I will be ordering for carry out next time. I hate to write a negative review but this has happened three times consecutively to me with my American and Indian friends and every time, I am disappointed by the restaurant management. I do not disagree with the previous negative reviews of this restaurant. I wish them good luck  and I hope that it retains chefs.  Without them, this place is nothing but bamboo and a fireplace connecting another Indian restaurant.

Worst Chinese Food!!!

It was a Christmas Day. I and my family decided to go to this restaurant named Bamboo Garden, located in Alpharetta, Georgia. We order tom-yum soup, chili chicken, Singapore rice and chicken 65 fried rice. We found hair in our soup. Besides, the other dishes were tasteless and the service was extremely poor. The waiter did not even apologize and just waved off the bill only for the soup. I did not say anything to him, but wanted to highlight that situation to everybody. I strongly recommend not to visit Bamboo Garden, ironically, specialized in Pan Asian Chinese Cuisine. Do not waste your money.
If you are looking for Indian and Indo-Chinese lunch buffet, then definitely one of the best place in Alpharetta. Ambience is great, buffet selection is very good and so does the price.

The Non-Vegetarian food is really amazing.  The Vegetarian food is not up to the mark.   Food is very reasonable priced and the food portions are also a little bit small.  You will get lot of items for a reasonable price.  The food tastes really good.  People really crowd this place especially in the week-ends.  A must go place when you are in Atlanta.
Chicken 65 is worth the hype. Tried their signature Chicken Kalimirch and it was delicious. The prices are less and quality is pretty high. Well done.

Good food. Horrible wait time. Order via phone or online to receive your order in a timely fashion. Ask what the wait time is at the counter or don’t be surprised if you end up standing for 45 minutes.

A no frills, self serve restaurant with the right portions, cost and delightful food. Amazing Gobi Manchurian, butter chicken and soft naans. Will certainly drop in to try more. It lived up to the expectations built by my colleagues who had  been there before.

Quick easy and super tasty Indian food. Order at the counter, then claim a table, grab a pitcher and fill it with water. Depending on your spice tolerance you may need more than one pitcher of water. :) And don't forget to order naan. Helps with the heat too. Setting is perfect for families with kids.
